The paper focuses on network coding in a wireless network, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of a linear program and decentralized algorithm suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests a possible fit with machine learning (cs.LG).
